description:
&lt;p&gt;Interested in supporting your local community?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come and join us at AWP Mental Health Trust and become an NHS hero.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are very proud of our amazing staff, who are continuing to work throughout the COVID19 pandemic, supporting people with mental health issues across the region.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for new colleagues, with a passion for helping people, to join us as Healthcare Support Workers in our team based at Southmead Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with our multi disciplinary team you will support up to 23 service users from across the region as they transition through their care pathway.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will receive training to complete the NHS Care Certificate and a Level 3 Healthcare apprenticeship. If you have some experience of caring work already that would be great – but if not, we will support you to develop the skills and experience needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an NHS employee you will have a wide range of benefits and discounts, access to the NHS pension scheme and a generous annual leave entitlement. Best of all you will have the reward of doing a job that really matters, with colleagues who care.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please get in touch, we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Emily Bond, Ward Manager, 0117 414 6630&lt;/p&gt;
